    "review_guidelines": "When evaluating complications of portal hypertension, always consider the primary management strategy. For variceal bleeding, the spectrum of care ranges from endoscopic to interventional radiology to surgical, with surgery being a frequent necessity for a subset of patients. For encephalopathy, the focus is overwhelmingly on medical management.",
