    "review_guidelines": "When evaluating a young man with gynecomastia, the initial steps should include a detailed history and physical examination to assess the duration, symptoms (pain, tenderness), and any associated findings. A focused endocrine workup, including serum hormone levels (testosterone, LH, FSH, prolactin, estradiol, hCG), is crucial to identify potential underlying etiologies such as hypogonadism, hyperprolactinemia, or androgen-secreting tumors. Imaging, such as ultrasound, may be helpful in select cases to assess breast tissue and rule out malignancy, though it's not typically the first-line diagnostic tool for benign gynecomastia.",
