    "verified_answer": "D",
    "set_the_stage": "This case presents a classic presentation of hemarthrosis in a young patient with factor VIII deficiency. Hemarthrosis, bleeding into a joint, is a significant complication and can lead to long-term joint damage if not promptly addressed. The key here is understanding the pathophysiology and the most effective immediate and long-term management.",
